\description{
Creates a declarative configuration object that drives
\code{config_table_ui()} / \code{config_table_server()}. The config describes
which rows and columns appear, which picker widget each column uses,
and how cross-column interactions (mutual exclusion, fill-down,
gating) work.
}
\details{
Two modes are supported:

\strong{Static mode} (default): rows are fixed at config time via
\code{row_keys} / \code{row_labels}. Use when the set of editable rows is
known up front (e.g. a grade roster).

\strong{Dynamic mode}: rows are derived at runtime from a reactive
\code{source_data} data frame passed to \code{\link[=config_table_server]{config_table_server()}}. Enable
by supplying \code{row_id_col} and either \code{row_label_col} or
\code{row_label_fn}. In this mode \code{row_keys} / \code{row_labels} are
optional (default to \code{character(0)}).
\subsection{Interactions}{

\code{interactions$mutual_exclusion}: a list of rules, each a list with
\code{when_on} (column ID), \code{clears} (column ID), and \code{display} (HTML
string to show in the cleared column's cell).

\code{interactions$fill_down}: a list with \code{column} (column ID),
\code{range_check_fn} (optional function \verb{(row_key, value) -> logical}
that returns \code{TRUE} when the row is in range for fill-down), and
optionally \code{input_name} (character — the Shiny input name the
widget JS sends; defaults to \code{paste0(column, "_fill_down")}).
}

\subsection{Gating}{

Columns with \code{gate} conditions (set via \code{widget_col(gate = ...)})
are automatically disabled until all conditions are met. Controller
columns referenced in \code{gate} conditions are automatically marked
\code{triggers_rerender = TRUE} so the table updates when they change.
}

\subsection{Dynamic mode}{

When \code{row_id_col} is non-NULL, the config is in dynamic mode.
Rows are not fixed at config time — they are derived from the
\code{source_data} reactive at runtime. Each time \code{source_data}
changes, the module merges the new row set with existing state:
user-entered values for rows that survive are preserved, new rows
receive \code{empty_value} defaults, and departed rows' state is
retained internally so it restores if those rows reappear.
}

\subsection{Appendable mode}{

When \code{appendable} is \code{TRUE}, the table becomes a variable-length
input collector where the \strong{user} controls the row set — adding
blank rows, deleting individual rows, and optionally resetting to
the minimum. This is mutually exclusive with dynamic mode.

Row keys are generated automatically as
\code{"row_1"}, \code{"row_2"}, … (incrementing, never reused in a
session). The module renders "Add Row" and per-row "Delete"
buttons. \code{min_rows} seeds the initial table and prevents deletion
below that count. \code{max_rows} caps the upper bound.
}
